      <h2>2. Stardew Valley</h2>
      <p><span style="color: #6c6e98ff;">Escape to the countryside and build the farm of your dreams in this serene playthrough.</span></p>
      <p>Stardew Valley is the game I go to when I just need to chill. It’s slow in the best way with watering crops, talking to villagers, fishing at night- it all brings back a feeling of nostalgia to me, despite having only bought the game 3 years ago. The little routines turn into something really cozy, and I love how much personality the town has once you get to know everyone.</p>
