      <h2>1. Hollow Knight</h2>
      <p><span style="color: #6c6e98ff;">A beautiful hand-drawn adventure through a vast underground world of bugs.</span></p>
      <p>I love how Hollow Knight pulls you into its world without saying much. The atmosphere and music build a lonely world waiting for the player to explore it. The movement feels super smooth, the art design is beautiful, and every time you think you’ve seen it all, there’s another hidden area waiting. It’s one of my favourite games of all time that I'll always take any chance to bring up.</p>
